        System.out.println("Washing dishes...");
    }

    public void vacuumFloor() {
        System.out.println("Vacuuming floor...");
    }
}
```
In this example, `Machine` is an interface that defines the methods that all machines should have (in this case, washing dishes and vacuuming the floor). The classes `Dishwasher` and `VacuumCleaner` are then implementations of this interface. They provide their own implementation for these methods.

